    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hi @jmotes-lapero,\r\n\r\nThank you for raising this issue.\r\n\r\nI had a look, and the issue is because the `fallbackComponent` provided to `DynamicWidgets` is an inline component, so the reference changes each render which makes it remount thus clearing the state.\r\nOur [documentation does show the proper usage](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/dynamic-facets/react-hooks/#widget-param-fallbackcomponent) although maybe we should mention it should be a stable reference.\r\n\r\nSo the problem is not related to the router itself but the usage of `DynamicWidgets`, and can be fixed just by changing this line : \r\n```diff\r\n<DynamicWidgets\r\n  facets={[]} \r\n-  fallbackComponent={(props) => <RefinementList {...props} />}\r\n+  fallbackComponent={RefinementList}\r\n/>\r\n```\r\nMy guess is maybe you're seeing it now because `react-instantsearch-hooks-router-nextjs` does a `push` with the Next.js router, which rerenders the whole page whereas before it wouldn't and `fallbackComponent` would have stayed the same.",
