    "body": "Thanks for the quick reply @aymeric-giraudet! This did indeed fix my minimal reproduction.\r\n\r\n~~However, the issue originated in a codebase that doesn't use DynamicWidgets at all - it just loops over an array of hardcoded refinements and renders a custom `<RefinementList />` (that's built using the useRefinements hook) directly. Any ideas on how to fix it there? Do I need to add the DynamicWidgets component to my main project?~~\r\n\r\nEdit: Nevermind! I'll try to create another minimal reproduction that illustrates the issue there. I tried adding a simple loop to this repo and it still worked fine.",
